author: Ashley Strickland, CNN
title: NASA astronaut, Russian cosmonauts will launch to the space station during a pandemic
description: Two Russian cosmonauts and a NASA astronaut will launch to the International Space Station early Thursday morning. NASA and Roscosmos, the Russian Space Agency, have closely followed protocol to ensure that the astronauts were quarantined ahead of launch.
content:
(CNN)Two Russian cosmonauts, Anatoli Ivanishin and Ivan Vagner, and NASA astronaut Chris Cassidy are expected to launch to the International Space Station from the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan on Thursday morning at 4:05 a.m. ET.
